Diversified Consumer Services

Company Overview of McCarthy Tétrault LLP



SnapshotPeople 




OverviewBoard MembersCommittees



Executive Profile
Thomas B. Akin  Senior Partner, McCarthy Tétrault LLPAgeTotal Calculated CompensationThis person is connected to 0 Board Members in 0 different organizations across 1 different industries.----
Background

		Mr. Thomas B. Akin is currently employed at McCarthy Tétrault LLP in the position of Senior Partner. He practises in all major areas of taxation, with special emphasis on transfer pricing, tax litigation and tax dispute resolution, domestic and international organizations, GST and provincial sales tax. Mr. Akin has been recognized by the International Tax Review as one of Canada’s top 10 tax advisors and by Chambers Global as a leading tax advisor and tax litigation ... specialist. He also appears in Euromoney Legal Media Group’s Guide to the World’s Leading Tax Lawyers, its 2006 Guide to the World’s Leading Transfer Pricing Advisers and in the International Tax Review’s World Tax 2005, as a leading adviser in the areas of transfer pricing, tax controversy, and indirect taxes. Mr. Akin appears in all editions of the Guide to the Leading 500 Lawyers in Canada, published by Lexpert and American Lawyer. He also appears in the 2006 Canadian Legal Lexpert Directory, a guide to the leading law firms and practitioners in Canada, in the areas of tax litigation, corporate tax and indirect tax. Articles and conference papers authored by him cover a variety of income tax, sales and commodity tax and customs and trade matters. Mr. Akin is chair of the Tax Court Bench and Bar Committee, International Fiscal Association (Canadian Branch) Councillor and past chair of the Canadian International Trade Tribunal Bench and Bar Committee and of the Metropolitan Toronto Board of Trade Tax Committee. Mr. Akin was also a member of the Canada Customs and Revenue Agency Appeals Advisory Committee and has been an elected member of the Council of the Ontario Bar Association. In addition, he is an editor of the CCH Canadian GST & Commodity Tax Cases. Mr. Akin was a member of the Tax Reform Sales Tax Advisory Committee to the Minister of Finance of Canada and was chair of the National Sales and Commodity Tax Section of the Canadian Bar Association and of the International Trade Committee of the Metropolitan Toronto Board of Trade. Mr. Akin graduated from Dalhousie University with his B.Sc. in 1972 and his MBA in 1974. He received his LLB from Dalhousie University in 1977.Read Full Background




